JUnit tests are a way to verify that a method is correctly performing its task.

Right click on the IntroToJUnitTest package. Select New->JUnit Test Case.

Click OK to add the JUnit Library.

Run the program. 

Did you see the red bar? 

Delete the call to the fail method and run it again.

Did you see a green bar?

Ask your teacher to explain: 
assertEquals(Object, Object);
assertFalse(Object);
assertTrue(Object);
